      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CASH AND COINS (2) stalked the lead from a middle box before hitting the front turning and lifting to score (25.17) at this track in a Mix over 440m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. PRETTY BOY FLOYD (4) jumped from box 1 last time and ran away with an impressive win scoring by 5 lengths at this track in a handy 24.85. Has the squeeze box to overcome and will need the breaks early. Solid formlines coming through his last run. One of main contenders. ASHBY MOCHA (1) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at this track over 440m behind Al's Memory (25.72) in a Grade 5. Worth another chance. ZIPPING BANGALOW (5) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can make amends.",
